A former Speaker of the House of Representatives in the Second Republic, Benjamin Akaai Chaha, is dead. It was learnt that Chaha died on Tuesday in Makurdi, the Benue State capital, after an illness. He was the second Speaker of the House of Representatives in the Shehu Shagari administration, after Edwin Ume-Ezeoke.   ‘Seven men raped 13-year-old’     Imo Assembly swears in Ngor Okpala representative     Aviation fuel scarcity, price hike disrupt flights…   Following the military putsch that overthrew the Shagari administration in December 1983, Chaha returned to his Zaki Biam ancestral home, where he remained until his illness that led to his demise. The ex-Speaker was a community leader who lived a quiet life devoid of controversy. He is survived by many children, including two lawyers.